<h3 class="page-header" id="idempotent-requests">Idempotent requests</h3>

<p>The API requires every <code>distinct_id</code> to be unique on the <a href="/reference/message">Message</a>, <a href="/reference/conversation">Conversation</a> and <a href="/reference/interlocutor">Interlocutor</a> resources. By doing so, the API supports idempotency for safely retrying requests without accidentally performing the same operation twice. For example, if a request to create a message fails due to a network connection error, you can retry the request with the same <code>distinct_id</code> and it is guaranteed that only a single message will be created.</p>
